WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:01:55.615 --> 00:01:57.367
Ok. go on through.

3
00:02:17.095 --> 00:02:19.180
All metal objects into the tray.

4
00:02:21.224 --> 00:02:22.600
Purpose of visit?

5
00:02:23.518 --> 00:02:26.354
A patient pick up and transfer to Smith's Grove.

6
00:02:26.896 --> 00:02:28.481
You're late.
- Yeah. 

7
00:02:28.690 --> 00:02:30.525
Should be on the road.
- Yeah.

8
00:02:30.650 --> 00:02:32.610
Hell of a night. huh?
- Real charmer.

9
00:02:32.736 --> 00:02:35.238
Yeah. I'll take you down there.
- All right.

10
00:02:35.363 --> 00:02:36.990
Let them in.
- Ok.

11
00:02:42.620 --> 00:02:45.040
First time here. huh?
- Hope it's the last time.

12
00:02:45.165 --> 00:02:47.709
You never get used to the faces. Never.

13
00:02:52.380 --> 00:02:53.840
Jesus!

14
00:02:55.342 --> 00:02:58.011
Jesus ain't got nothing to do with this place.

15
00:02:59.012 --> 00:03:00.013
Come on.

16
00:03:09.606 --> 00:03:13.193
Yeah. this is where the society
dumps its worst nightmares.

17
00:03:16.946 --> 00:03:18.156
Yeah the one you're picking up ...

18
00:03:18.907 --> 00:03:21.618
Just thinking about him
gives me the willies.

19
00:03:21.951 --> 00:03:24.162
A decade ago. Halloween night ...

20
00:03:24.287 --> 00:03:27.248
He murdered 16 people ...
maybe more.

21
00:03:27.374 --> 00:03:28.708
Trying to get to his sister.

22
00:03:29.417 --> 00:03:31.002
Nearly got her too. 

23
00:03:31.211 --> 00:03:33.421
But his doctor ... of all people.

24
00:03:33.546 --> 00:03:35.674
shot him ... six times.

25
00:03:35.965 --> 00:03:37.592
Then he set him on fire. 

26
00:03:37.717 --> 00:03:39.803
Both of them nearly burned to death.

27
00:03:40.303 --> 00:03:44.015
Yeah. I'll be glad to see this one gone.
Yes. indeedy!

28
00:03:48.520 --> 00:03:50.063
Welcome to Hell.

29
00:03:53.858 --> 00:03:55.151
Doctor?
- Yes?

30
00:03:55.276 --> 00:03:57.320
The transfer personnel are here.

31
00:04:01.449 --> 00:04:03.326
Smith's Grove?
- Yes.

32
00:04:03.451 --> 00:04:06.204
I'm Dr. Hoffman. medical administrator.

33
00:04:06.329 --> 00:04:08.581
Has he been prepped?
- Ready to go.

34
00:04:08.832 --> 00:04:10.250
Who signs for him?

35
00:04:10.542 --> 00:04:11.418
I do.

36
00:04:11.876 --> 00:04:13.044
Outside.

37
00:04:13.211 --> 00:04:14.462
Check him out.

38
00:04:49.247 --> 00:04:51.499
I'd assumed Dr. Loomis would be here.

39
00:04:51.624 --> 00:04:54.169
Michael Myers is still his patient.

40
00:04:54.294 --> 00:04:56.671
Well. if Loomis read memos. he'd be here.

41
00:04:56.796 --> 00:05:00.383
Fortunately his position is more ceremonial than medical.

42
00:05:00.508 --> 00:05:02.135
And with Myers gone ...

43
00:05:02.510 --> 00:05:05.388
My hope is that he'll either transfer ...

44
00:05:05.513 --> 00:05:07.140
retire...

45
00:05:09.309 --> 00:05:10.769
or die.

46
00:05:14.773 --> 00:05:17.150
All right. let's move him.

47
00:05:28.495 --> 00:05:29.454
Watch it.

48
00:05:29.704 --> 00:05:30.664
I got this end.

49
00:05:31.039 --> 00:05:36.503
I can safely say that Michael Myers is now in your hands.
- Yeah. I guess you're happy to see him go.

50
00:05:38.672 --> 00:05:40.882
Locked and loaded.
- Let's roll.

51
00:05:42.217 --> 00:05:43.009
Night. doc.

52
00:05:43.134 --> 00:05:44.678
Drive carefully.

53
00:06:14.874 --> 00:06:18.086
Did Hoffman say anything about living relatives?
- Yeah.

54
00:06:18.211 --> 00:06:20.338
A niece living in his hometown.

55
00:06:22.465 --> 00:06:23.341
And?

56
00:06:23.925 --> 00:06:26.636
"And?" She's too young to be his legal ward.

57
00:06:27.095 --> 00:06:29.931
So the state owns him?
Great.

58
00:06:31.516 --> 00:06:33.393
You know. I still don't understand.

59
00:06:40.859 --> 00:06:43.945
No!

60
00:07:02.964 --> 00:07:04.049
Kido ...

61
00:07:05.008 --> 00:07:07.010
It's 4:00 in the morning.

62
00:07:07.135 --> 00:07:08.887
I can't sleep.

63
00:07:09.179 --> 00:07:11.181
What is this?
Four nights in a row?

64
00:07:11.723 --> 00:07:15.685
You going for a record here?
The seven-year-old insomniac's hall of fame?

65
00:07:15.935 --> 00:07:17.729
Do you love me. Rachel?

66
00:07:18.688 --> 00:07:22.609
Serious questions tonight.
Of course I love you.

67
00:07:22.776 --> 00:07:24.194
Like a sister?

68
00:07:24.527 --> 00:07:27.655
Jamie. sometimes it's ...
- Like a real sister?

69
00:07:28.823 --> 00:07:31.451
We're not really sisters. Jamie.

70
00:07:32.035 --> 00:07:34.954
But that doesn't mean that I love you any less.

71
00:07:37.832 --> 00:07:39.459
Sure it does.

72
00:07:41.252 --> 00:07:46.424
I know you miss your parents. It hasn't been that long.
- It's been 11 months.

73
00:07:48.051 --> 00:07:51.805
Your mother used to baby-sit me when I was your age.
I'll bet you didn't know that.

74
00:07:51.930 --> 00:07:55.350
You're lucky.
I wish she could do the same for me.

75
00:07:57.435 --> 00:07:59.854
Come on. Jamie.
Let's go back to bed.

76
00:08:00.397 --> 00:08:01.314
Come on. Sunday.

77
00:08:10.824 --> 00:08:14.202
Sleep tight.
We'll have French toast for breakfast. ok?

78
00:08:14.619 --> 00:08:15.453
Nighty-night.

79
00:08:15.578 --> 00:08:16.746
Come on. Sunday.

80
00:08:17.539 --> 00:08:18.623
Nighty-night.

81
00:09:31.946 --> 00:09:36.076
Now I lay me down to sleep.
I pray the Lord my soul to keep.

82
00:09:36.201 --> 00:09:40.413
If I should die before I wake.
I pray the Lord my soul will take.

83
00:09:40.664 --> 00:09:43.041
God bless 
Mr. and Mrs. Corruthers.

84
00:09:43.166 --> 00:09:46.961
God bless Rachel. God bless Sunday. God bless me.

85
00:09:47.087 --> 00:09:50.840
And God bless mommy and daddy in heaven. Amen.

86
00:10:57.782 --> 00:11:01.202
Help me please!
Somebody help me!

87
00:11:01.328 --> 00:11:03.455
Help me!

88
00:11:07.250 --> 00:11:09.377
Jamie!

89
00:11:15.508 --> 00:11:20.430
Oh. dear God!
It's all right. sweetheart.

90
00:11:21.097 --> 00:11:25.435
A bad dream. That's all.
Just a nasty old dream.

91
00:11:26.102 --> 00:11:28.688
I've got you.
You're safe now. see?

92
00:11:28.897 --> 00:11:31.191
It's okay. baby. It's okay.

93
00:11:31.316 --> 00:11:34.235
It's okay. Shh.

94
00:11:34.736 --> 00:11:38.323
You're gonna be just fine.
It's okay. baby. You're gonna be fine.

95
00:12:02.389 --> 00:12:04.265
Damn it!
Darlene!

96
00:12:06.393 --> 00:12:10.063
There's a clean one in the laundry
room next to your blue slacks. Hello?

97
00:12:10.605 --> 00:12:14.025
Honey. this tie's got a spot on it.
I can't wear this today. I got a 10:30 with Chuck.

98
00:12:14.150 --> 00:12:17.487
Hang on. Mrs. Pierce.
Not that tie. On the other side.

99
00:12:17.612 --> 00:12:19.531
That's not the only thing
you're eating. Rachel!

100
00:12:19.656 --> 00:12:23.410
Mom. I'm on a diet. You want an oinker for a daughter?
- Found it.

101
00:12:23.535 --> 00:12:24.411
Sorry. 

102
00:12:24.536 --> 00:12:27.372
Do you suppose Susan could just bring her crutches?

103
00:12:28.456 --> 00:12:31.835
Stupid question.
Tell her I hope she feels better.

104
00:12:33.586 --> 00:12:35.797
Susan's mother.
She can't baby-sit tonight.

105
00:12:35.922 --> 00:12:36.673
Why not? 

106
00:12:36.798 --> 00:12:39.342
Susan broke her ankle last night at the ice rink.

107
00:12:41.428 --> 00:12:43.972
Rachel?
- Mom. please.

108
00:12:44.848 --> 00:12:46.766
You'll have to watch Jamie tonight.

109
00:12:46.891 --> 00:12:49.978
Not tonight. I've got that date with Brady.
You know how important that is.

110
00:12:50.103 --> 00:12:52.605
Well. Tonight is very important for your father and me.

111
00:12:52.731 --> 00:12:55.567
Can't you find somebody else?
- It's too late.

112
00:12:55.692 --> 00:12:57.318
What am I supposed to tell Brady?

113
00:12:57.444 --> 00:13:01.114
"Sorry. but I've got to baby-sit my foster sister.
Go and have fun by yourself."

114
00:13:01.239 --> 00:13:03.908
It's not exactly the end of the world for goodness' sake.
- Oh. sure it is.

115
00:13:04.826 --> 00:13:07.454
I think tonight Brady was ready to make a commitment.

116
00:13:07.579 --> 00:13:09.914
But now. my future relationship
my engagement ...

117
00:13:10.498 --> 00:13:15.337
my marriage. my children and your grandchildren
have all been wiped out. because I have to baby-sit.

118
00:13:16.421 --> 00:13:20.258
I'm sorry I ruined everything.
If I wasn't here. you could go out.

119
00:13:23.011 --> 00:13:24.262
Good job. Rachel.

120
00:13:24.387 --> 00:13:27.390
That little girl needs all the love
we can give her right now.

121
00:13:27.640 --> 00:13:29.976
And all you can do is think about yourself?

122
00:13:38.026 --> 00:13:38.860
Jamie?

123
00:13:44.407 --> 00:13:47.494
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean it like that.

124
00:13:47.744 --> 00:13:50.830
I can go out with Brady tomorrow night.
It's no big deal.

125
00:13:50.955 --> 00:13:54.209
But you wanted to go out tonight.
It's my fault you can't.

126
00:13:54.334 --> 00:13:57.921
Well. tonight we're going to do something better.
We're going to go trick-or-treating.

127
00:13:58.046 --> 00:13:59.464
I don't want to. 

128
00:13:59.798 --> 00:14:04.511
It's Halloween! I mean: don't you want to get dressed up
in a really scary costume and get some candy?

129
00:14:08.848 --> 00:14:12.560
How 'bout this afternoon I pick you up
from school and we go get ice cream?

130
00:14:13.186 --> 00:14:14.688
Double scoops?

131
00:14:15.397 --> 00:14:18.191
Double scoops.
Now let's get some breakfast.

132
00:14:21.194 --> 00:14:23.988
Dr. Quinn. call 7402.

133
00:14:38.586 --> 00:14:39.879
Why wasn't I notified?

134
00:14:40.005 --> 00:14:43.174
About what?
- You know damn well about what.

135
00:14:43.550 --> 00:14:45.885
You let them take it out of here.

136
00:14:46.011 --> 00:14:50.223
For Christ's sake. spare me the speech.
I've listened to it for a decade.

137
00:14:50.390 --> 00:14:56.229
The fact is that Michael Myers was a federal patient and
a federal prisoner. Therefore he's subject to federal law.

138
00:14:56.354 --> 00:15:03.695
We're not talking about any ordinary prisoner. Hoffman.
We are talking about an evil on two legs.

139
00:15:04.237 --> 00:15:06.322
I can see this is useless.

140
00:15:07.240 --> 00:15:08.950
Do you know what today is?

141
00:15:09.993 --> 00:15:11.411
Do you know the date?

142
00:15:12.996 --> 00:15:15.415
Every day I look at myself in the mirror and ...

143
00:15:15.540 --> 00:15:17.459
And every day I remember.

144
00:15:18.543 --> 00:15:20.754
Look at me ... Hoffman!

145
00:15:21.046 --> 00:15:22.630
Take a good look!

146
00:15:25.800 --> 00:15:29.179
I don't want anyone to have to live
through that night again.

147
00:15:30.847 --> 00:15:35.018
I've said this before.
I think you're the one who needs mental help.

148
00:15:41.566 --> 00:15:43.693
Yes? Dr. Hoffman.

149
00:15:47.364 --> 00:15:48.698
I see.

150
00:15:49.824 --> 00:15:51.409
I see. Thank you.

151
00:15:53.787 --> 00:15:58.625
Apparently there was an accident
just south of Mill Creek near the bri ... Loomis?

152
00:15:59.125 --> 00:16:00.293
Loomis!

153
00:16:23.983 --> 00:16:24.859
Is that it?

154
00:16:24.984 --> 00:16:26.820
Yes.
- When did this happen?

155
00:16:26.945 --> 00:16:31.074
Sometime in the night. They probably lost the road
in the storm. Come down the embankment. It happens. 

156
00:16:31.199 --> 00:16:33.576
An accident?
- Yes. sir.
- Do you believe that?

157
00:16:33.702 --> 00:16:34.869
Why shouldn't I?

158
00:16:34.995 --> 00:16:36.830
How many people in the bus? 

159
00:16:37.038 --> 00:16:38.873
Four ... plus Myers.

160
00:16:42.627 --> 00:16:46.589
How many bodies did you find?
- It's hard to tell. they're all chewed up.

161
00:16:50.510 --> 00:16:51.428
Loomis?

162
00:16:52.178 --> 00:16:53.805
It's over. Leave it alone.

163
00:17:20.498 --> 00:17:21.708
He's gone.

164
00:17:22.542 --> 00:17:23.626
He was here ...

165
00:17:23.752 --> 00:17:25.045
... but he's gone.

166
00:17:25.170 --> 00:17:26.838
Did you find any other bodies? 

167
00:17:26.963 --> 00:17:30.091
Not yet. There's a lot of ground to cover.
- You won't find him.

168
00:17:30.884 --> 00:17:32.594
He's done all this.

169
00:17:33.011 --> 00:17:35.805
Now he's escaped.
- You don't know that.

170
00:17:35.930 --> 00:17:38.183
Michael could've been thrown from the bus.

171
00:17:38.308 --> 00:17:41.102
I've seen bodies thrown 50 - 60 feet from a crash site.

172
00:17:41.227 --> 00:17:44.773
Even if by some miracle Michael's conscious ...

173
00:17:44.898 --> 00:17:50.362
his ... his muscles would be totally useless.
Give the troopers a chance to search.

174
00:17:50.487 --> 00:17:53.615
You're talking about him as if he were a human being.

175
00:17:54.366 --> 00:17:57.369
That part of him died years ago.

176
00:17:58.787 --> 00:18:00.789
Now where are you going?

177
00:18:01.164 --> 00:18:02.374
Haddonfield.

178
00:18:02.499 --> 00:18:04.417
It's a four hour drive.

179
00:18:04.542 --> 00:18:06.878
You can reach me through the local police.

180
00:18:07.003 --> 00:18:09.881
If you don't find him in four hours ... 

181
00:18:10.048 --> 00:18:11.925
I'm sure I will.

182
00:18:22.227 --> 00:18:25.689
Hey Gar. How 'bout a 9/16 socket over here?

183
00:19:00.849 --> 00:19:02.684
Hey! Hey there!

184
00:19:02.976 --> 00:19:03.852
Hello!

185
00:19:46.061 --> 00:19:47.145
Hello?

186
00:19:49.481 --> 00:19:50.357
Hello?

187
00:19:51.775 --> 00:19:53.026
Is anybody here?

188
00:19:57.030 --> 00:19:57.947
Hello?

189
00:20:02.494 --> 00:20:03.328
Hello!

190
00:20:26.267 --> 00:20:27.769
Is anybody here?

191
00:20:43.493 --> 00:20:44.995
God in heaven.

192
00:21:05.432 --> 00:21:06.599
Michael?

193
00:21:12.605 --> 00:21:13.898
Why now?

194
00:21:18.153 --> 00:21:19.821
You waited ten years.

195
00:21:20.780 --> 00:21:22.699
I knew this day would come.

196
00:21:23.742 --> 00:21:26.036
Don't go to Haddonfield.

197
00:21:28.621 --> 00:21:30.957
If you want another victim. take me.

198
00:21:32.792 --> 00:21:35.628
But leave those people in peace.

199
00:21:37.922 --> 00:21:39.049
Please ...

200
00:21:40.133 --> 00:21:41.343
Michael.

201
00:21:43.887 --> 00:21:45.430
Goddamn you.

202
00:22:08.161 --> 00:22:09.788
Michael!

203
00:22:49.327 --> 00:22:51.830
Hey Jamie!
Where's your costume?

204
00:22:52.080 --> 00:22:56.292
Where's your mask? Or are you wearing it?
- I don't need to wear a stupid costume!

205
00:22:56.418 --> 00:23:01.464
That's because every day is Halloween at Jamie's house.
Right. Jamie? - 'Cause your uncle's the boogeyman.

206
00:23:01.589 --> 00:23:05.885
Boogeyman! Boogeyman!
Jamie's uncle's the boogeyman!

207
00:23:06.011 --> 00:23:11.016
How come your mommy
didn't make you a costume. Jamie?
- How could she? Her mommy's dead.

208
00:23:11.141 --> 00:23:13.351
Jamie's mommy's ... a mummy!

209
00:23:13.476 --> 00:23:15.437
Stop it! Okay?
Stop it!

210
00:23:15.562 --> 00:23:22.027
Jamie's an orphan! Jamie's an orphan!
- Stop it! Please. stop it!

211
00:23:22.152 --> 00:23:26.406
Jamie's an orphan! Jamie's an orphan!

212
00:23:26.531 --> 00:23:30.785
Jamie's uncle's the boogeyman!
Jamie's an orphan!

213
00:23:30.910 --> 00:23:32.704
Every day is Halloween at Jamie's house.

214
00:23:32.829 --> 00:23:36.833
Boogeyman! Boogeyman! Boogeyman!

215
00:23:37.208 --> 00:23:40.837
... didn't make you ...?
- How could she? Her mommy's dead.

216
00:23:47.177 --> 00:23:49.596
You're okay. you're okay.

217
00:23:53.391 --> 00:23:54.351
Jamie!

218
00:23:56.978 --> 00:23:58.772
Jamie. are you okay?

219
00:24:07.614 --> 00:24:09.282
You remember Lindsey. don't you?

220
00:24:09.407 --> 00:24:11.076
Hi Jamie.
- Yeah. hi.

221
00:24:11.201 --> 00:24:12.994
You ready for some ice cream?

222
00:24:14.371 --> 00:24:17.874
I wanna go trick-or-treating ...
like the other kids.

223
00:24:18.041 --> 00:24:20.585
But I thought you didn't wanna go trick-or-treating.

224
00:24:22.170 --> 00:24:25.548
You know Rach. discount mart's
having a sale on Halloween costumes.

225
00:24:25.924 --> 00:24:28.802
No. Brady's working there till 6:00 today.
- I know.

226
00:24:28.927 --> 00:24:29.886
Don't you wanna talk to him?

227
00:24:30.095 --> 00:24:32.597
I don't wanna look pushy.
- You won't look pushy.

228
00:24:32.722 --> 00:24:34.182
Well. I don't wanna come on too strong.

229
00:24:34.307 --> 00:24:37.977
A guy hates a girl that comes on too strong.
Fragile egos. and all of that.

230
00:24:38.103 --> 00:24:39.854
You won't come on too strong.

231
00:24:39.979 --> 00:24:42.524
Well. I don't wanna seem desperate or anything.

232
00:24:42.649 --> 00:24:44.901
Face it Rach. you are desperate.

233
00:24:46.820 --> 00:24:49.739
You're just gonna go in and buy a costume for Jamie.
Perfectly legit.

234
00:24:49.864 --> 00:24:51.282
I don't know.

235
00:24:51.741 --> 00:24:52.867
Well ...

236
00:24:53.034 --> 00:24:55.662
Do I drop you at the discount mart or the Dairy Queen?

237
00:24:56.329 --> 00:24:57.747
Jamie?

238
00:24:58.540 --> 00:25:01.793
Discount mart.
Can we get an ice cream after?

239
00:25:02.669 --> 00:25:04.004
You bet.

240
00:25:29.362 --> 00:25:31.031
Hey. Wade. Why don't you go ahead
and make your move? 

241
00:25:31.156 --> 00:25:32.615
Don't rush me. Brady.

242
00:25:32.741 --> 00:25:34.451
Timing's gotta be premo.

243
00:25:34.576 --> 00:25:37.620
Yeah well. money talks and bullshit walks.
You know what I mean?

244
00:25:37.787 --> 00:25:39.998
Double or nothing. you don't ask Kelly out.

245
00:25:41.207 --> 00:25:43.084
All right. Ten bucks.
Let's see it.

246
00:25:44.377 --> 00:25:45.837
He's not gonna do it.

247
00:25:46.087 --> 00:25:49.257
Chicken. - Don't forget. man.
She's Sheriff Meeker's daughter.

248
00:25:51.468 --> 00:25:53.011
Her daddy don't scare me.

249
